Uganda’s Robert Kyagulanyi Ssentamu, popularly known as Bobi Wine, of the National Unity Platform (NUP), on Friday said he was still pondering on whether to go to the country’s Supreme Court to challenge the outcome of the 2021 presidential election which saw Mr Yoweri Museveni declared winner.
Museveni, 76, of the ruling National Resistance Movement (NRM), was on January 16 declared winner of the presidential election with 5,851,037 votes, representing 58.64 per cent, against KWine’s 3,475,298 votes, representing 34.85 per cent.



