The musician-turned-politician declared that the vote was rigged even before the final tally was announced by the Electoral Commission Chairman Justice Simon Byabakama.
Although Wine indicated his willingness to challenge the results, his party officials, in an interview with the Daily Monitor, said they are not enthusiastic about it.



