Dismissed petition
The Supreme Court Coram that was made of nine Justices unanimously dismissed the petition for lack of merit. Just days to filing the petition, unknown people broke into the offices of Fred Muwema, who was the lead counsel representing the petitioner, and ran away with all the affidavits that were supporting the petition.
The nine Justices who dismissed Mbabazi’s petition included Bart Katureebe, Lilian
“Having made a due inquiry into the petition, and on the basis of our findings…we hereby declare that the 1st respondent [Museveni] was validly elected as president in accordance with Article 104 of the constitution and Section 59 of the Presidential Elections Act. Accordingly, this petition is dismissed with no orders as to cost,” the 2016 judgment read.
Can they overturn a presidential election? 
Most people who spoke to the Daily Monitor for this article believe that it is an uphill task to overturn a presidential election in Uganda.
In his memoir titled ‘Blessing and Joy of Who You Are’, Justice Kanyeihamba who was part of the panel which decided the 2006 election, says before the judgment was finally read by the then Chief Justice Benjamin Odoki, four out of seven Justices had decided to overturn the election.



